title: Sample Book, Summit Road, 1960–61
description: Hard cover binding in brown, mustard and white, covered with stencil pattern from CUM 1940-120-43 and superimposed with title: "Summit Road". A handle for carrying is attached to the spine. The book contains twenty-four examples, some of which are 18th and 19th century American in origin. "Wedgewood" is derived from CUM buttons, 1931-6-3-a,c,d,f,h,j and "Dorcester" from a CUM wall stencil design, 1940-120-43.

tombstone.epitaph: Sample Book, Summit Road, 1960–61; Manufactured by S.M. Hexter Company ; USA; machine-printed; 52 x 51.5 cm (20 1/2 x 20 1/4 in.); Gift of S.M. Hexter Company; 1961-33-1-1/105
